<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>出版物 |皮尤研究中心</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/publications/</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 01:09:17 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>美国人首先从哪里获取突发新闻信息？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/24/where-do-americans-turn-first-for-information-about-breaking-news/</link><description>当突发新闻事件发生时，36% 的美国成年人表示，他们通常会首先向自己喜欢的新闻机构寻求更多信息。</description><pubDate>Wed, 25 Mar 2026 01:09:16 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/24/where-do-americans-turn-first-for-information-about-breaking-news/</guid></item><item><title>大约十分之六的美国人在道义上不反对临终医疗救助</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/23/about-6-in-10-americans-dont-have-moral-objections-to-medical-aid-in-dying/</link><description>共和党人认为医生协助死亡在道德上是错误的可能性是民主党人的两倍（48% vs. 23%）。</description><pubDate>Tue, 24 Mar 2026 01:04:15 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/23/about-6-in-10-americans-dont-have-moral-objections-to-medical-aid-in-dying/</guid></item><item><title>关于美国黑人移民的主要发现</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/20/key-findings-about-black-immigrants-in-the-us/</link><description>自2000年以来，美国黑人移民人口增加了一倍多，到2024年将达到560万，目前占黑人总人口的11.4%。</description><pubDate>Sat, 21 Mar 2026 01:02:55 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/20/key-findings-about-black-immigrants-in-the-us/</guid></item><item><title>大多数美国人更喜欢拥有大房子的分散社区</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/19/majority-of-americans-prefer-spread-out-communities-with-big-houses/</link><description>55% 的美国人表示，他们更愿意居住在房屋更大、距离便利设施更远的社区，而 44% 的人则持相反观点。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 01:06:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/19/majority-of-americans-prefer-spread-out-communities-with-big-houses/</guid></item><item><title>美国人认为什么是不道德的？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2026/03/19/what-do-americans-consider-immoral/</link><description>十分之九的美国人认为外遇是错误的。共和党和民主党在堕胎和同性恋的道德问题上存在巨大分歧。</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 00:51:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/2026/03/19/what-do-americans-consider-immoral/</guid></item><item><title>美国男人和女人如何度过他们的时间？</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/feature/how-do-u-s-men-and-women-spend-their-time/</link><description>探索美国人如何按性别和年龄组分配时间。</description><pubDate>Wed, 18 Mar 2026 01:11:01 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/social-trends/feature/how-do-u-s-men-and-women-spend-their-time/</guid></item><item><title>与许多其他国家的人相比，美国人不太可能认为赌博在道德上是错误的</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/16/americans-are-less-likely-than-people-in-many-other-countries-to-see-gambling-as-morally-wrong/</link><description>在许多其他接受调查的国家，大约一半或更多的成年人认为赌博是不道德的。其中印度尼西亚为 89%，印度为 83%，意大利为 71%。</description><pubDate>Tue, 17 Mar 2026 01:07:11 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/16/americans-are-less-likely-than-people-in-many-other-countries-to-see-gambling-as-morally-wrong/</guid></item><item><title>特朗普重返办公室第一年联邦劳动力减少10%</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/13/federal-workforce-shrank-10-in-trumps-first-year-back-in-office/</link><description>2025 年，联邦劳动力将减少 10.3%，失去近 238,000 名工人。在主要机构中，教育部和美国国际开发署的削减幅度最大。</description><pubDate>Sat, 14 Mar 2026 01:04:51 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/short-reads/2026/03/13/federal-workforce-shrank-10-in-trumps-first-year-back-in-office/</guid></item><item><title>大多数美国人仍然认为堕胎在所有或大多数情况下都应该合法</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/03/12/majority-of-americans-continue-to-say-abortion-should-be-legal-in-all-or-most-cases/</link><description>60% 的大多数美国成年人表示，在所有或大多数情况下堕胎应该是合法的。这一比例较过去几年略有下降。</description><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 01:10:27 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/politics/2026/03/12/majority-of-americans-continue-to-say-abortion-should-be-legal-in-all-or-most-cases/</guid></item><item><title>公众对堕胎的看法</title><link>https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/fact-sheet/public-opinion-on-abortion/</link><description>堕胎在美国长期以来一直是一个有争议的问题，也是美国人在党派、意识形态和宗教方面产生严重分歧的一个问题。</description><pubDate>Fri, 13 Jun 2025 00:53:18 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.pewresearch.org/religion/fact-sheet/public-opinion-on-abortion/</guid></item></channel></rss>